LAGOS – The Federal Government through the Ministry Of Foreign Affairs, Abuja on Monday announced opportunities for the placement of Nigerian students affected by the conflict in Ukraine into tertiary institutions across the country. The move by the government is to enable the returnee students displaced by the ongoing war between Russia and Ukraine to continue their education in tertiary institutions in the country. A statement signed by Mrs. Francisca K. Omayuli, Spokesperson, Ministry of Foreign Affairs explained that the window of opportunities is open to interested Nigerian students from Ukraine to act between 4th to 15th July 2022 and furnish the Ministry with the required information. The statement is titled: “The Federal Government of Nigeria Facilitates Admission into Nigerian Tertiary institutions for Nigerian Students Affected by the conflict in Ukraine”. It reads in part: “The Federal Government of Nigeria wishes to inform Nigerian students who returned from Ukraine following the conflict in that country, that efforts are being made to facilitate their placement into various Nigerian tertiary institutions, to enable them to continue their studies. “In this connection, interested students should visit the Ministry of Foreign Affairs website: https://www.foreignaffairs.gov.ng and complete the online Nigerian Student in Ukraine (NSU) registration form with the required information on or before 15h July, 2022.” Details later.